@startuml mesmerize-sqs-fire-and-forget
title Mesmerize — SQS Fire-and-Forget (Async)\nADR-014 · NFR durable engagement / audit facts

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false

participant "Publisher\n(e.g. device-realtime\nor session-service)" as Pub
queue "engagement.events" as Evt
participant "engagement-service" as Eng
queue "audit.events" as Aud
participant "audit-telemetry-service" as Audit

Pub -> Evt : SendMessage\nmessageType=engagement.recorded\ntenantId, clinicId?, sessionId,\ncontentId, icd10, duration…\n(**no** replyTo / no wait)
Pub -> Pub : Continue immediately\n(fire-and-forget)

Evt -> Eng : ReceiveMessage
Eng -> Eng : Persist engagement\n(de-identified)

Pub -> Aud : SendMessage\nmessageType=audit.append\n(optional parallel fact)
Aud -> Audit : ReceiveMessage
Audit -> Audit : Write diagnostic/audit store\n(no PHI)

note over Pub, Eng
  Use for: session.ended, engagement.recorded,
  device.command.acked, audit events.
  Publisher does **not** block on consumer success;
  durability via SQS + retries + DLQ (see diagram 16).
end note

@enduml
